  <refnamediv>
    <refname>fft2pad</refname>
    <refpurpose>Pad smaller matrix with zeros to the given size before transformation.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   y = fft2pad(x,r,c)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>x :</term>
      <listitem><para> Source matrix</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>r :</term>
      <listitem><para> Number of rows for the output image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>c :</term>
      <listitem><para> Number of columns for the output image</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>y :</term>
      <listitem><para> Output matric with rxc size</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
FFT2PAD will pad the input matrix to the given r x c size, and perform fft2
after the padding. This will yield the output matrix at the same size given.
This is useful in the frequency domain filtering.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
x = testmatrix('magic',5);
y = fft2pad(x,8,8);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

